                     /synonym="Gateway attP1"
                     /synonym="lambda-derived attP (specificity 1)"
                     /note="Gateway recombinational-cloning attP site,
                     specificity 1; 232 bp donor-vector attachment site.
                     Engineered, lambda-derived attP site: it keeps the
                     bacteriophage lambda attP architecture (P and P' arm
                     Int-binding sites and IHF sites flanking the common core)
                     with a central 7 bp overlap modified to set its
                     recombination specificity. The BP reaction (lambda Int +
                     IHF) recombines attB1 with attP1 to give attL1 + attR1.
                     Source: pDONR221 positions 570-801 (+ strand)."
                     /db_xref="SO:0000057"
